cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on container orchestration frameworks that are used for managing complex distributed applications. It also touches upon software engineering (cs.SE) aspects such as feature comparison and investigating the maturity and stability of the frameworks. The paper discusses network plugin architectures, which falls under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The study also covers system support for improved cluster security and container security, which can be categorized under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential areas for further evolution and innovation, which can be classified under Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
